## PHASE 1 — RESEARCH

**A. Local research.** Work out what's actually true for this niche in this city:
- Real local reasons customers need this service here (climate, weather, soil, housing
  age, seasonality, regulations — whatever genuinely applies)
- Real nearby towns/suburbs in the region this business would serve
- Things that are NOT true of this city that a generic template might wrongly include
  (e.g. a landlocked city has no coastal weather; a warm city has no snow load).
  Keep a running "never mention" list and obey it for the entire build.

**B. Competitor analysis.** Read every site in the chosen niche folder. For each:
pages, services/sub-services, topics per page, every FAQ, approximate word counts,
trust signals and content angles.

**C. Coverage map.**
- Union of ALL topics/services/FAQs across competitors
- Gaps: covered by only one competitor
- Missing: covered by none but customers would search for
- Highest word count reached per page type (this is the floor to beat)

**D. Content plan.** Cover everything they cover PLUS the gaps, at 2–3x depth:
full page list, sections + target word count per page, full FAQ list.

Print the local research, coverage map, and content plan as a short summary, then
**continue automatically** to Phase 2. Do not wait for approval unless something is
genuinely ambiguous.

---

## PHASE 2 — DESIGN EXTRACTION

From the chosen Design folder, study the screenshot + real CSS and extract the ACTUAL
values (never guess):
- Exact hex color palette
- Typography: families, weights, sizes, line-heights. Use Google Fonts equivalents;
  substitute a similar free font for any licensed one and tell me which.
- Spacing scale, container widths, section padding
- Button styles, card styles, shadows, radii
- Section rhythm and dividers (angled/curved/straight — match it)
- Header/nav layout, footer layout, hero composition
- Overall density (airy vs dense) — match it

Write all tokens as CSS custom properties at the top of one shared `/css/style.css`
so the site can be re-skinned later by changing only those variables.

**DO NOT COPY** from the reference: business name, logo, copy, images, icons, brand
badges, reviews, ratings, addresses, team photos, JS, or tracking. Design language
only, fresh markup.

---

## PHASE 3 — BUILD

Plain static HTML. No React, no frameworks, no build step. All text must be real HTML
in the file — nothing JavaScript-rendered.

**Structure** (one folder per page, each with `index.html`, for clean URLs):
```
/                       /residential            /commercial
/[service-1] … /[service-7 or 8]                /blog
/blog/[4–6 posts]       /about                  /contact
/thank-you              /privacy                /terms
/css/style.css          /sitemap.xml            /robots.txt
/contact.php
```

`contact.php`: fields Name, Phone, Email, Service, Message; honeypot field named
`website`; emails the owner address from Phase 0; redirects to `/thank-you/`.

**Home page sections in order:** hero (H1 "[Service] in [City], [State]" + subhead +
click-to-call + quote form) → trust strip → services grid → "Signs You Need [Service]"
→ step-by-step process → why choose us → service area (real nearby towns) → FAQ →
final CTA + form.

**Write the real content** from the Phase 1 plan — do not leave placeholders. Home
~1,500 words, each service page ~1,000 words, blog posts ~800 words. Depth means
broader coverage and more specific local detail, never filler or repetition.
Original wording throughout — never copy competitor sentences.

**SEO on every page:** unique title `[Page Service] in [City], [State] | [Business]`,
exactly one H1, unique meta description, canonical + Open Graph, LocalBusiness JSON-LD
in the footer, correct heading order, internal links between related pages, image
placeholders with descriptive alt text using the city, `loading="lazy"` below the fold.

**Identical footer NAP on every page, byte-for-byte:**
`[Business] — Serving [City] & [Region], [State] — [Phone]`

**Always include:** sticky header with logo area, nav, and a large tappable
click-to-call button; short quote form in every footer; full form on `/contact`;
mobile-first and fast-loading.

**Animations:** AOS via CDN (fade-up on sections/cards/FAQ with slight stagger),
CSS hover transitions on buttons and cards, smooth-scroll anchors, respect
`prefers-reduced-motion`.

---

## HARD RULES (apply to every phase)

**Honesty — this is a brand-new site with no operating history.** Never include, even
if the design reference or competitors have them:
- Team/staff/founder photos, or people presented as employees
- Certifications, licenses, badges, awards, accreditations
- Reviews, testimonials, star ratings, review counts
- A street address (city and region only)
- Project gallery or past-work section
- Years in business, employee counts, financing offers
- Guaranteed response times ("on site in 60 minutes")
- Any claim of owning crews, trucks, technicians, or equipment

Frame the business as **connecting callers with vetted local pros**. Never use
first-person "we do the work" phrasing ("our crews," "truck-mounted extractors pull
out the water"). Attribute physical work to the local pros.

Allowed trust claims only: 24/7 service (if the niche warrants), free estimates,
fast local response.

Where the design reference has a reviews or team section, replace it with
"Why Choose Us" or an educational section.

